&= \frac{A(x - 3)(x - 5) + \color{red}{B}(x - 2)(x - 5) + \color{blue}{C}(x - 2)(x - 3)}{(x - 2)(x - 3)(x - 5)}
\end{align}</start>

Hence, we have
\begin{align}A(x - 3)(x - 5) &+ \color{red}{B}(x - 2)(x - 5) + \color{blue}{C}(x - 2)(x - 3) = x^2 - 7\pmod{(x - 2)(x - 3)(x - 5)}.\\
A(x^2 - 8x + 15) &+ B(x^2 - 7x + 10) + C(x^2 - 5x + 6) = x^2 - 7\pmod{(x - 2)(x - 3)(x - 5)}.
\end{align}

Assuming $x=2,$ we get
\begin{align}
A(4 - 16 + 15) + B(4 - 14 + 10) + C(4 - 10 + 6) &= -7,\\
B &= -7.
\end{align}

Assuming $x=3,$ we get
\begin{align}
A(9 - 24 + 15) + B(9 - 21 + 10) + C(9 - 15 + 6) &= -10,\\
A &= -10.
\end{align}

Assuming $x=5,$ we get
\begin{align}
A(25 - 40 + 15) + B(25 - 35 + 10) + C(25 - 25 + 6) &= 18,\\
C &= 18.
\end{align}

Thus, the ordered triple $(A,B,C)$ is $\boxed{(-10,-7,18)}.$</answer>

